# QA Report ‚Äî Sprint M4: Instagram Per-Slide Body-Text Override + Slide-1 Cover-Centering
<!-- Evaluator: Sonnet 4.6 (adversarial spec review, R7 pass) -->
<!-- Date: 2026-05-03 -->
<!-- Verdict: NEEDS WORK ‚Äî 5 High + 3 Medium + 3 Low -->

---

## [FAIL] HIGH ‚Äî B3: `textOverride` alignment in SlideTemplate is ambiguous

**What is missing:** B3 says the Body-Region renders `textOverride` as a "zentrierter Text-Container". A3 says "Body-Blocks bleiben links-b√ºndig" ‚Äî auto-body is always `textAlign: "left"`, no exceptions. B3 says the override block uses "gleiche Font/Size/Line-Height wie Auto-Body" but the alignment qualifier "zentrierter" directly contradicts A3's left-aligned rule.

**What a developer will implement:** Either (a) `textAlign: "center"` for textOverride (literal reading of "zentrierter"), or (b) `textAlign: "left"` to match auto-body. Either choice could be argued from the spec. Developer will pick one; there's a 50% chance it's wrong.

**Why it matters:** Preview renders override text with different alignment than auto-render ‚Üí visual inconsistency between auto and manual mode. DK-7 visual smoke will flag it. Codex R1 finding.

**Fix needed:** B3 must state explicitly: `textAlign: "left"` (consistent with A3 auto-body left-alignment). Replace "zentrierter Text-Container" with "left-aligned, same as auto-body blocks".

---

## [FAIL] HIGH ‚Äî B8 / E5: `422 body_too_long` vs Zod `400` ‚Äî validation layer not specified

**What is missing:** B8 says `textOverride` exceeding 10000 chars ‚Üí `422 body_too_long`. E5 tests this: `PUT mit textOverride l√§nger als 10000 ‚Üí 422 body_too_long`. But Zod's `z.string().max(10000)` produces a 400 response (standard Zod validation failure), not a 422. The spec never states whether the length check lives in the Zod schema (`z.string().max(10000)`) or as a handler-level check after Zod parse.

**What a developer will implement:** They will use `z.string().max(10000).optional()` in the Zod schema (natural choice). Zod returns 400. E5 test `expect(status).toBe(422)` fails. Developer is confused and must guess at the fix.

**Same problem for `override_empty`:** `422 override_empty` for `textOverride === ""` ‚Äî Zod `z.string().min(1)` would return 400 with generic message, not 422 with custom code.

**Fix needed:** Spec must state: Zod schema uses `z.string().optional()` (no length/empty constraint in Zod). After Zod safeParse succeeds, handler explicitly checks:
```ts
if (slide.textOverride !== undefined && slide.textOverride.length === 0)
  return NextResponse.json({ error: "override_empty" }, { status: 422 });
if (slide.textOverride !== undefined && slide.textOverride.length > MAX_BODY_CHARS_PER_SLIDE)
  return NextResponse.json({ error: "body_too_long" }, { status: 422 });
```

