## [FAIL] HIGH ‚Äî E3: Third bullet "leadOnSlide: false auf allen text-slides bei grid-path" doesn't name which function

**What is missing:** E3 has four bullets. Bullet 3: "`leadOnSlide`-Flag: false auf allen text-slides bei grid-path". Bullet 4: "Stored-leadOnSlide-Override-Test: ... `buildManualSlides`-output ... `slide.leadOnSlide === false`". Bullet 4 explicitly names `buildManualSlides`. Bullet 3 does not name any function. A developer reads bullet 3 as "also a test for `buildManualSlides`" because that's the only function named in this context.

**What gets missed:** `splitAgendaIntoSlides` (auto-path renderer) also needs `leadOnSlide: false` on text-slides at grid-path. Files-to-Change item (g) says "NICHT NUR `buildManualSlides`" but the test for `splitAgendaIntoSlides` is not explicitly required in E3. Without a test for the auto-path, a developer can ship a `splitAgendaIntoSlides` that still sets `leadOnSlide: true` on the first text-slide, causing double-Lead render (on Slide 1 grid AND on Slide 2 text) in the auto-render path.

**Fix needed:** E3 bullet 3 must read: "**`splitAgendaIntoSlides` (auto-path)**: `leadOnSlide === false` for all text-slides when `hasGrid === true`. This is SEPARATE from bullet 4 which tests `buildManualSlides` (manual-path)."

