## [FAIL] MEDIUM ‚Äî B6 + B6c: Stale-detection Promise.all placement not shown relative to branch structure

**What is missing:** B6 shows the stale-detection `Promise.all` code block. B6c shows the branch structure (`if (mode === "manual") ... else if (mode === "stale") ... else ...`). The spec says "stale-detection runs in BOTH modes" but never shows the combined code: WHERE inside the manual-branch and WHERE inside the stale-branch does the Promise.all run? After `buildManualSlidesForEditor`? Before or after `textSlides` assembly?

**What a developer will implement:** The Promise.all needs `manualSlidesForEditor` and `contentById` map ‚Äî both of which are assembled inside the `if (storedOverride)` branches. A developer might (a) run stale-detection only in the manual-branch (missing stale-branch), (b) run it outside the branches (before `manualSlidesForEditor` exists ‚Üí undefined), or (c) run it correctly in both branches but duplicate the code.

**Fix needed:** B6 or B6c must show a single combined code sketch that places the Promise.all within each branch after `manualSlidesForEditor` is built, making the "BOTH modes" requirement concrete. Or: extract stale-detection into a named helper function `computeStaleSlides(manualSlidesForEditor, contentById)` that both branches call.

