## [FAIL] LOW ‚Äî E6: No test for `fonts_unavailable` 500 path

**What is missing:** D1 explicitly specifies: `if (!fontsResult.ok) return NextResponse.json({error: "fonts_unavailable"}, {status: 500})`. E6 test list (6 items) does not include `POST when font file missing ‚Üí 500 fonts_unavailable`.

**What a developer will implement:** Error path exists in code (spec requires it) but is never exercised by tests. A developer might implement `return NextResponse.json({error: "font_load_failed"}, ...)` (wrong error code) or omit the `{ok: false}` guard entirely. No test catches it.

**Fix needed:** Add E6 bullet: "POST when `loadInstagramFonts` returns `{ok: false}` ‚Üí 500 `fonts_unavailable` (mock `loadInstagramFonts` to return `{ok: false, weight: 800, error: new Error()}`)"

---

## [FAIL] LOW ‚Äî D3b/D4: Blob-URL revoke on Save path has no E4 test

**What is missing:** D3b specifies three revoke scenarios: (a) cache-replace, (b) modal-unmount, (c) Save (D4). E4 D3b tests only (a) and (b). The Save revoke (before cache-clear, D4) has no test.

**What a developer will implement:** They may forget to revoke blob-URLs before clearing the cache on Save, causing a memory leak for heavy users who save frequently (5+ preview slides √ó multiple saves per session).

**Fix needed:** Add E4 bullet: "D3b-Test (c): Save-trigger clears preview cache with URL.revokeObjectURL for all existing entries before clearing (verify via vi.spyOn(URL, 'revokeObjectURL') ‚Äî spy.mock.calls.length === prePopulatedCacheSize before POST-to-save)."

---

## [FAIL] LOW ‚Äî C7c: `acknowledgedStaleSlides` Set reset after Save has no E4 test

**What is missing:** C7c says: "Bei Save (D4) wird Set gecleart". If the Set is not cleared after Save, a previously acknowledged slide that remains stale (content changed again before save) would not show the banner on re-fetch, because the Set would still mark it as acknowledged. No E4 test verifies the Set is cleared after Save.

**Fix needed:** Add E4 bullet: "After Save completes (PUT response received, GET re-fetch done), `acknowledgedStaleSlides` Set is empty ‚Äî a stale slide in the re-fetched serverState.staleSlides DOES show the banner again (Set was cleared, not just reset-via-GET)."

---

## Verdict

**NEEDS WORK**

5 High + 3 Medium + 3 Low findings. Two findings (B3 alignment ambiguity, B5 encoding) will produce incorrect behavior visible in DK-7 visual smoke. Three findings (B8 status-code layer, E3 splitAgendaIntoSlides test gap, D3 postPreview stale-closure) are known Codex R1 finding patterns from this codebase (PR #110 R1 P2, lessons.md escapeHtml-idempotency, PR #137 useCallback deps). Fix High findings before implementation starts.
